Four men are believed to have suffered from drug overdoses during a party cruise on Sydney Harbour . 
  Two 21-year-olds and a 25 and 22- year-old collapsed on the vessel on Good Friday . 
  They were rushed to St Vincent's Hospital where they are now stable . 
  Police believe the men took a dangerous strain of ecstasy pills known as 'blue scissors' About 800 partygoers poured off the Bella Vista boat near the Opera House . 
  Police say they discovered cocaine, marijuana and MDMA before the boat left . 
 